Package me.clarius.sdk.mobileapi

Class ProcessedImageInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • me.clarius.sdk.mobileapi.ProcessedImageInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable
    public class ProcessedImageInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable
    Processed image information supplied with each frame.

    The originX and originY fields contain the scan-converted image’s origin coordinates expressed in the probe’s referential. The image’s origin is the top-left corner; the probe’s referential is the middle of its imaging surface, X increases horizontally toward the right, Y increases vertically toward the bottom. This is useful to compute what part of the acquired image is being rendered by the Clarius App when the user scales/translates the display.
